[src:python/asyncio-task] Return the list of stack frames for this Task.
[src:python/asyncio-task] If the wrapped coroutine is not done, this returns the stack where it is suspended.
[src:python/asyncio-task] If the coroutine has completed successfully or was cancelled, this returns an empty list.
[src:python/asyncio-task] If the coroutine was terminated by an exception, this returns the list of traceback frames.
[src:python/asyncio-task] The frames are always ordered from oldest to newest.
[src:python/asyncio-task] Only one stack frame is returned for a suspended coroutine.
[src:python/asyncio-task] The optional *limit* argument sets the maximum number of frames to return; by default all available frames are returned.
