[src:python/datetime-p02] Return the current UTC date and time, with `tzinfo` `None`.
[src:python/datetime-p02] This is like `now()`, but returns the current UTC date and time, as a naive `datetime` object.
[src:python/datetime-p02] An aware current UTC datetime can be obtained by calling `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`.
[src:python/datetime-p02] Because naive `datetime` objects are treated by many `datetime` methods as local times, it is preferred to use aware datetimes to represent times in UTC.
[src:python/datetime-p02] As such, the recommended way to create an object representing the current time in UTC is by calling `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`.
