[src:python/datetime-p02] If both are aware and have different `tzinfo` attributes, `a-b` acts as if `a` and `b` were first converted to naive UTC datetimes.
[src:python/datetime-p02] The result is `(a.replace(tzinfo=None) - a.utcoffset()) - (b.replace(tzinfo=None) - b.utcoffset())` except that the implementation never overflows.
